        <div class="repair-appliance">GE Monogram Advantium ZSC2202NSS — Beverly Hills</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Food Heating But Not Browning — Three Previous Service Calls</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">30" Advantium wall oven — owner had been through three other service companies over six months. Two had replaced components (one replaced the magnetron, one replaced the convection element) — neither fixed the browning problem. We tested the halogen lamp assembly current draw on arrival: the lamps were drawing 40% of rated current — still on, but well into degraded output territory. This is the classic Advantium halogen failure pattern: enough output to heat the food, not enough to brown the surface. The previous technicians had both tested the magnetron (normal) and moved on to other components. Replaced the halogen lamp assembly with OEM GE Monogram part. First Advantium cook after service: perfect browning. Owner had been living with this for six months.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: Halogen lamp assembly OEM · Time: 1.5 hours · Same Day</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">GE Monogram Column Refrigerator ZIRS360NNRH — Bel Air</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Running 6°F Warm — Two Previous Sealed System Services</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">36" column refrigerator in a custom cabinetry suite — two previous companies had performed sealed system work (one recharged refrigerant, one replaced the temperature sensor). Both repairs lasted 3–4 weeks before the unit returned to running warm. We measured condenser clearance before touching anything: 0.5" rear clearance against the back cabinet wall — Monogram specifies minimum 1.5". The entire previous-service history was fighting a symptom, not a cause. Repositioned the column unit forward 1.25" using the built-in adjustment feet, bringing clearance to 1.75". Temperature back to setpoint within 4 hours, no parts required. This is the most satisfying type of Monogram call — the client saves thousands compared to continuing the sealed-system cycle.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: None (clearance adjustment) · Time: 1 hour · Same Day</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">GE Monogram ZGP366SETSS Range — Pacific Palisades</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Two Front Burners Dead, SmartHQ Error Code 22</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">36" professional range — two front burners not igniting. SmartHQ app had been logging error code 22 (igniter circuit fault) for the front left burner for two weeks before the second burner failed. Pacific Palisades coastal location. Both front igniters had salt-air corrosion on the ceramic tips — the coastal proximity had accelerated the corrosion significantly. Replaced both igniters with OEM GE Monogram high-BTU specific igniters (front burners on this model are 20,000 BTU and use a different igniter spec than the rear burners). Also inspected and cleaned the rear burner igniters — two showing early corrosion. Replaced all four for a complete set. Owner enrolled in annual coastal service going forward.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: 4× OEM igniters (full set) · Time: 2 hours · Same Day</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">GE Monogram ZDWC240LII Dishwasher — West Hollywood</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Custom Panel Detached, Not Draining</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">Panel-ready Monogram dishwasher — two issues. The custom panel had pulled away from the door (alarming, but a bracket failure). The unit also wasn't draining. Detached panel: the panel attachment bracket had cracked — common on heavily used panel-ready dishwashers where the panel adds significant door weight. Replaced the bracket assembly (OEM). Drainage: drain pump impeller had debris blocking it — cleared and tested. Both issues resolved in one visit. Also performed full spray arm cleaning (LA hard water scale, 275 ppm West Hollywood water). Dishwasher running quietly and draining completely. Owner noted three other companies had declined to service it because of the panel situation.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: Panel bracket OEM · Time: 1.5 hours · Same Day</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">GE Monogram Statement ZWE23ESSNSS Oven — Santa Monica</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Door Rubbing Against Cabinetry, Seal Worn</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">Statement Collection 30" wall oven — door had been rubbing against the right side of the cabinet surround for 8 months. Owner had attributed this to the door gasket failing and had replaced the gasket twice. The gasket wasn't the cause — the oven had shifted 2mm right in the cabinet opening (home settlement, the oven was 4 years old in a 2-year-old renovation). Realigned the oven within the cabinet opening using the Statement Collection's built-in alignment adjustment — brought the right clearance back to spec. The gasket had been damaged by the rubbing and needed replacement (third time, but now with the correct underlying cause resolved). No more contact with the cabinetry after alignment.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: Door gasket OEM · Time: 1 hour · Same Day</div>
      </div>

      <div class="repair-item">
        <div class="repair-appliance">GE Monogram Column Suite ZIBS360 + ZIFS360 — Malibu</div>
        <div class="repair-issue">Both Columns Running Warm After Santa Ana Event</div>
        <div class="repair-detail">Paired 36" refrigerator and freezer column suite in a Malibu coastal property. Both units began running warm simultaneously after a Santa Ana wind event. Simultaneous failure across both columns ruled out individual sealed-system faults. Inspected both condenser coils: both coils were loaded with fine ash and dust from the Santa Ana event, which had blown in through the condenser air intake at the cabinet base. Full coil cleaning on both units — the ash was significant and had reduced airflow substantially. Both units returned to setpoint temperature within 3 hours. Also sealed the condenser intake gap with a filter mesh to reduce future ash intake during wind events — a recommendation we make for all coastal and hillside Monogram installations.</div>
        <div class="repair-meta">Parts: Filter mesh (preventive) · Time: 2 hours · Same Day</div>
      </div>
    </div>
