<!-- 09 — FAQ -->
<section class="section section-gray">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <div class="section-num">09 — FAQ</div>
    <h2 class="section-title">GE Monogram Repair FAQ</h2>

    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">What is the difference between GE Monogram and GE Profile?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">GE Profile is GE's upper-mid tier — smart connectivity, premium performance. GE Monogram is the luxury tier above Profile: panel-ready built-in designs, column refrigeration suites, the Advantium speed oven, and Statement Collection flush installations. Monogram requires different service knowledge — particularly around built-in clearance requirements and the Advantium system.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Why does my GE Monogram column refrigerator keep running warm even after being serviced?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">In most LA custom kitchen cases: inadequate condenser clearance behind the cabinetry. Monogram column refrigerators require 1.5" minimum rear clearance. When cabinetry is built tighter than this, the condenser overheats and the unit runs warm regardless of sealed-system repairs. We measure clearances before any other diagnosis on every Monogram column refrigerator call. Many "running warm" cases resolve without parts once the clearance is corrected.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">My Advantium heats food but it won't brown — what's wrong?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Almost certainly the halogen lamp assembly. The Advantium's quartz halogen lamps degrade after 500–800 cook cycles — they stay functional enough to heat but lose the output needed for surface browning. This is the most common Advantium fault and the most commonly misdiagnosed. We test halogen current draw first on every Advantium call. Halogen assembly replacement resolves this in the vast majority of cases.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Do you service the full Monogram column suite — refrigerator, freezer, wine, and beverage?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">Yes — complete column suite service in a single visit. When multiple columns in a suite show problems simultaneously, we diagnose at the suite level first (shared circuit, shared ventilation constraint) before individual column diagnosis. This approach is more efficient and more accurate than treating each column as a separate service call.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">Is GE Monogram still made by GE?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">GE Appliances (including Monogram) was acquired by Haier in 2016. It continues to operate as GE Appliances, a Haier company, with US-based manufacturing. Parts availability is excellent — current Monogram models have access to both the established GE supply network and Haier's global manufacturing supply chain.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <div class="faq-q">My custom panel fell off my Monogram dishwasher — do I need a new dishwasher?</div>
        <div class="faq-a">No — this is almost always the panel attachment bracket, a separate serviceable component from the main door latch. The bracket holds the custom panel to the door and fails independently. We carry common Monogram dishwasher panel brackets. This looks alarming but is a straightforward repair.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

